h3. Problem Description

It seems the driver is not handling {{readPreference}} as expected when specified in the connection string.

This affects both the current 3.6.3 release as well as the current 4.0.0 beta version.

After some input by Matt it turns out this is _not a duplicate of_ NODE-2807. The fix in NODE-2807 fixed it when being passed directly as an additional parameter when creating the {{MongoClient}}. However, when using _only_ the connection string, the {{readPreference}} is not parsed.

In short this does not work:

{code:javascript}
const client = await MongoClient.connect(
    'mongodb://root:password123@localhost:28001/?directConnection=true&readPreference=secondary'
);
{code}

This will work:

{code:javascript}
const client = await MongoClient.connect(
    'mongodb://root:password123@localhost:28001/?directConnection=true', { readPreference: 'secondary' }
);
{code}
 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new {{MongoClient}} instance by connecting to node specifying {{readPreference=secondary}} in the connection string, e.g.:
 {{mongodb://root:password@localhost:28001/?readPreference=secondary&directConnection=true}}
 # Print the value of {{client.readPreference.mode}}.

h3. Expected Results

The value is {{secondary}}.
h3. Actual Results

The value is {{primary}}.

